---
/**
 * now.astro — "Now" page inspired by nownownow.com.
 *
 * A snapshot of current priorities, projects, and focus areas.
 * Updated periodically to signal active engagement.
 *
 * Audience value:
 *   - KHS reviewers: signals current trajectory and priorities
 *   - PhD committees: shows active research direction
 *   - Collaborators: identifies areas open for partnership
 *   - General visitors: humanizes the author
 *
 * Content is hardcoded here rather than in a content collection because
 * it changes infrequently and should be edited directly.
 */
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout
  title="Now"
  subtitle="What I'm focused on right now."
  activeNav=""
>
  <p class="mb-8 text-xs text-[var(--color-muted)] font-mono">
    Last updated: April 2026 · Boston, MA
  </p>

  <div class="prose max-w-none">
    <h2>Research</h2>
    <p>
      Building interferometric imaging systems and physics-constrained inverse models at the
      <a href="https://octresearch.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Wellman Center for Photomedicine</a>
      (Harvard Medical School / MGH). Current work focuses on recovering optical
      properties from spectral measurements, spectral unmixing algorithms, and
      prototype broadband micro-LED systems.
    </p>

    <h2>PhD applications</h2>
    <p>
      Preparing applications for Fall 2027 entry. Research focus: quantum photonics,
      spin-photon interfaces, computational inverse design for nanophotonic devices,
      integrated photonic systems, and physics-informed deep learning. Exploring labs
      at MIT, Stanford, Caltech, and Harvard SEAS.
    </p>

    <h2>Podcast</h2>
    <p>
      Developing a science podcast exploring how fundamental physics innovation
      translates into technologies that solve grand challenges in health, energy,
      and information. Currently in pre-production: building the guest pipeline,
      production stack, and first episode scripts.
    </p>

    <h2>Ventures</h2>
    <p>
      Exploring deep-tech venture creation at the intersection of photonics,
      quantum sensing, and AI — translating physics research into commercially
      viable technologies.
    </p>

    <h2>Learning</h2>
    <p>
      Quantum computing fundamentals, Lean 4 theorem proving, advanced
      fiber optics, and the business mechanics of deep-tech company formation.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]">
    <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-muted)]">
      This page is inspired by <a href="https://nownownow.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[var(--color-link)] no-underline hover:underline">nownownow.com</a>.
      It's a snapshot of what I'm focused on at this point in my life.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
